</bold></th><th align="center"><bold>p</bold></th></tr></thead><tbody valign="top"><tr><td align="left" valign="bottom">EVLW group<hr/></td><td align="center" valign="bottom">2.783&#x02009;&#x000b1;&#x02009;0.452<hr/></td><td align="center" valign="bottom">2.667&#x02009;&#x000b1;&#x02009;0.654*<hr/></td><td align="center" valign="bottom">2.311&#x02009;&#x000b1;&#x02009;0.526*<hr/></td><td align="center" valign="bottom">1.867&#x02009;&#x000b1;&#x02009;0.516*<hr/></td><td align="center" valign="bottom">8.678<hr/></td><td align="center" valign="bottom">0.000<hr/></td></tr><tr><td align="left" valign="bottom">PAWP group<hr/></td><td align="center" valign="bottom">2.826&#x02009;&#x000b1;&#x02009;0.526<hr/></td><td align="center" valign="bottom">2.738&#x02009;&#x000b1;&#x02009;0.587*<hr/></td><td align="center" valign="bottom">2.381&#x02009;&#x000b1;&#x02009;0.582*<hr/></td><td align="center" valign="bottom">2.092&#x02009;&#x000b1;&#x02009;0.546*<hr/></td><td align="center" valign="bottom">5.092<hr/></td><td align="center" valign="bottom">0.003<hr/></td></tr><tr><td align="left" valign="bottom"><italic>t</italic><hr/></td><td align="center" valign="bottom">0.237<hr/></td><td align="center" valign="bottom">0.307<hr/></td><td align="center" valign="bottom">0.340<hr/></td><td align="center" valign="bottom">1.141<hr/></td><td align="center" valign="bottom">1.302<hr/></td><td align="center" valign="bottom">0.273<hr/></td></tr><tr><td align="left">p</td><td align="center">0.815</td><td align="center">0.761</td><td align="center">0.736</td><td align="center">0.264</td><td align="center">&#x000a0;</td><td align="center">&#x000a0;</td></tr></tbody></table><table-wrap-foot><p>Data are shown as mean&#x02009;&#x000b1;&#x02009;SD, *p&#x02009;&#x0003c;&#x02009;0.05 versus prior treatment.</p></table-wrap-foot></table-wrap></sec><sec><title>Oxygenation index</title><p>The oxygenation index dramatically enhanced in the EVLW and PAWP groups as the treatment was continued (p&#x02009;&#x0003c;&#x02009;0.05 for both groups). Significant differences were observed between the two groups (<italic>F</italic>&#x02009;=&#x02009;6.437, p&#x02009;=&#x02009;0.006; Table&#x000a0;<xref ref-type="table" rid="T4">4</xref>).</p><table-wrap position="float" id="T4"><label>Table 4</label><caption><p>Comparison of oxygenation index in the two groups</p></caption><table frame="hsides" rules="groups" border="1"><colgroup><col align="center"/><col align="center"/><col align="center"/><col align="center"/><col align="center"/><col align="center"/><col align="center"/><col align="center"/></colgroup><thead valign="top"><tr><th align="center"><bold>Groups</bold></th><th align="center"><bold>Prior treatment</bold></th><th align="center"><bold>The first day post- treatment</bold></th><th align="center"><bold>The third day post- treatment</bold></th><th align="center"><bold>The fifth day post- treatment</bold></th><th align="center"><bold>The fifth day post- treatment</bold></th><th align="center"><bold>
